                <h1>What Does the Devil Look Like? Unveiling the Myths and Mystique</h1>
                <p>The devil's appearance often draws from various cultural and artistic interpretations. Typically depicted with horns, a pointed tail, and red or black skin, he embodies evil and temptation. Some portray him as a suave, charming figure, while others show him in grotesque forms. Ultimately, his image reflects humanity's fears of the unknown.</p>
